#Watchers of the Dead (#1085): exile it - each opponent picks two graveyard
#cards to keep and exiles the rest. They keep bears+giant, the cadet goes.
[INIT]
firstmain
[PLAYER1]
inplay:watchers of the dead
[PLAYER2]
graveyard:grizzly bears,hill giant,eager cadet
[DO]
watchers of the dead
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
grizzly bears
goto firstmain
hill giant
goto firstmain
watchers of the dead
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
[ASSERT]
FIRSTMAIN
[PLAYER1]
exile:watchers of the dead
[PLAYER2]
graveyard:grizzly bears,hill giant
exile:eager cadet
[END]
#PARKED: opponent-chooser-on-my-turn family, 4th witness (parallax_nexus,
#Hollow Specter, Prowling Pangolin cousins). The self-exile cost works and the
#"moveto(exile) all(*|mygraveyard)" leg fires - ALL 3 cards exiled - but the
#opponent's <upto:2> keep-chooser (granted ability$!...!$ opponent) never
#accepts clicks (tried choice-0-first and direct-clicks+source-confirm), so
#the (blink) protection never lands. Net: strictly stronger than oracle
#(exiles everything).
